    eli5: "Imagine a robot that can run super fast, lift heavy things, and never gets tired. Sounds scary, right? But can that robot give you a hug when you are sad? Can it make up a funny story that makes you laugh? Can it be your best friend? Nope. Those are YOUR superpowers. The book says: stop trying to be more like a robot. Instead, be more like the best human you can be — kind, creative, brave, loving. That is what the world needs, and no robot can ever do it.",
